description: Prime chain of 128 terms, including 104 distinct primes, consisting of the output of eight equations that alternate sequentially within a procedural expression of a single polynomial. The equations are either subsequences of x^2 - 79x + 1601 or transforms with one exception: 100x^2 - 2260x + 12959. The other four distinct equations are Euler-derived: 25x^2 - 1185x + 14083, 25x^2 - 775x + 6047, 100x^2 - 2280x + 13159, 100x^2 - 4160x + 43427.
